==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crookes space
<hw>Crookes space</hw> <pr>(kr⟦oocr⟧ks)</pr>. <ety>[After Sir William
<etsep>Crookes</etsep>, English chemist, who first described it.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The dark space within the negative-pole glow
at the cathode of a vacuum tube, observed only when the pressure is low
enough to give a striated discharge; -- called also <altname>Crookes
layer</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crookes tube</ent>⟦br⟧
